nl_problem:
# Task: permutations_with_duplicates
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: permuteUnique(self, arg1)

Given a collection of numbers, nums, that might contain duplicates, return all possible unique permutations in any order.

Constraints:
- 1 <= nums.length <= 8
- -10 <= nums[i] <= 10
lisp_spec:
(task
 (name "permuteUnique")
 (signature ( (self) (arg1 (list int)) ) (list (list int)))
 (constraints
   (constraint "The length of nums is between 1 and 8, inclusive.")
   (constraint "Each element in nums is between -10 and 10, inclusive.")
 )
 (goal
   (description "Generate all unique permutations of the given list of numbers.")
   (rule "Return a list of lists where each inner list is a unique permutation of the input list.")
   (return "A list containing all unique permutations of the input list nums.")
 )
)
